cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.SD 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL) because it deals with the word sense disambiguation task for prepositions, which is a common problem in natural language processing. It could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories because the authors propose a mapping from preposition senses to relation labels, which involves machine learning techniques. Information retrieval (cs.IR) and software engineering (cs.SD) are also possible sub-categories because the inventory of preposition relations could be useful for information retrieval systems and software applications that deal with natural language processing.
